external_knowledge:
- `browser_id` is a unique identifier for each browser;
- `browser_name` is the name of the browser;
- `market_share` represents the current market share of the browser;
- `last_updated` indicates the date when the browser information was last updated.

- Market share is a measure of the browser's popularity relative to other browsers in the market;
- The latest version details include the version number, release date, number of downloads, bug fixes, and new features;
- Creator information includes the name and official website of the creator;
- Software license details include the name of the license and the URL to its documentation.

- "latest versions" refer to the most recent versions of the browsers as of the specified date range;
- "released within the calendar year 2022" means the release dates are between '2022-01-01' and '2022-12-31';
- "surpasses the wave of 5 million" means the average number of downloads is greater than 5,000,000.

- "latest version of each browser" refers to the most recent version of the browser as identified by the `latest_version_id` in the `browsers` table;
- "release details" include the version number, release date, download count, bug fixes, and new features;
- "creator's background" includes the name, description, founded year, headquarters, website, employee count, and last update date of the creator;
- "user-assigned tags" are the labels given to browsers by users, along with the names of the users who assigned them;
- "market influence" is represented by the market share fraction, which is the market share of the browser as a decimal.

- "Majestic ships" refers to web browsers;
- "Captains" refers to the creators of the browsers;
- "Voyages" refers to the latest versions of the browsers;
- "Market share" is a measure of the browser's popularity in the market;
- "User satisfaction" is represented by user ratings;
- "Contributions" are the number of contributions made to the browser;
- "Tags" are the number of tags associated with the browser;
- "Cumulative market share" is the running total of market share, ordered by browser.

- "dawn of the new year" refers to January 1, 2023;
- "most recently accessed" means the entries are ordered by the access date in descending order;
- The query limits the results to the top 10 entries.

sql:
SELECT b.browser_name, bv.version_number
FROM browsers b
INNER JOIN browser_versions bv ON b.latest_version_id = bv.version_id;

